    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - INSTALL - CLUTCH HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLUTCH HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Installation of the clutch housing is done in the horizontal position.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on the housing mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q9">Figure 269</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007q9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007q9" filename="../figg13/G13007Q9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 269. Install Clutch Housing on Front Box</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the clutch housing on the front box; pilot it on the six studs and drive gear
                bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q9">Figure 269</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the nuts with washers or lockwashers on the studs, and tighten to 180 to 190 ft-lbs.
                (244 to 258 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007r0">Figure 270</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007r0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007r0" filename="../figg13/G13007R0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 270. Install Bolts With Lockwashers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bolts with lockwashers. Tighten to 90 to 100 ft-lbs. (122 to 136 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007r0">Figure 270</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
